<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
The diploid number of this species was also 56 chromosomes (
<quantity box="[1056,1112,1104,1128]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" unit="m" value="24.0">24 m</quantity>
+ 20 sm + 6 st + 6 a) (
<figureCitation box="[1362,1437,1104,1128]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[136,175,1821,1845]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,183,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[136,1459,174,1805]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. Karyotypesarranged fromGiemsa-stained chromosomes.a. Pimelodusabsconditus; b. Pimelodusbritskii; c. Pimelodus maculatus; d. Pimelodus microstoma; e. Pimelodus mysteriosus; f. Pimelodus ortmanni; g. Pimelodus paranaensis. Pairs of the AgNORs and B chromosomes are in the boxes. Scales bar = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3709715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3709715/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
). The AgNORs were located in the terminal region of the long arm of a pair of subtelocentric chromosomes 23 (
<figureCitation box="[1314,1387,1168,1192]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[136,175,1821,1845]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,183,1796]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[136,1459,174,1805]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. Karyotypesarranged fromGiemsa-stained chromosomes.a. Pimelodusabsconditus; b. Pimelodusbritskii; c. Pimelodus maculatus; d. Pimelodus microstoma; e. Pimelodus mysteriosus; f. Pimelodus ortmanni; g. Pimelodus paranaensis. Pairs of the AgNORs and B chromosomes are in the boxes. Scales bar = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3709715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3709715/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
, box). C-banding revealed the existence of pale heterochromatin in the region of the telomeres of some chromosomes, with more conspicuous heterochromatin being found in the telomeric region of the short arm (pair 6) and long arm (pairs 17, 22, 23 and 24), in both telomeres (pair 8) and the pericentromeric region of the short arm (pairs 1 and 25) and in long arm in pair 21 (
<figureCitation box="[937,1016,1392,1416]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[129,166,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[151,1418,179,1823]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[128,1451,174,1832]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig.2. Karyotypesarranged from C-banded chromosomes.a. Pimelodusabsconditus; b. Pimelodus britskii; c. Pimelodus maculatus; d. Pimelodus microstoma; e. Pimelodus mysteriosus; f. Pimelodus ortmanni; g. Pimelodus paranaensis. B chromosomes in the boxes. Scales bar = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3709719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3709719/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
). The 18S rDNA and 5S rDNA showed syntenic sites in the terminal region of the long arm of a pair of subtelocentric chromosomes (23), which corresponds to the AgNORs (
<figureCitation box="[961,1036,1488,1512]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[136,179,1573,1597]" captionTargetBox="[136,1459,174,1558]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[136,1459,174,1558]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 3. Karyotypes after FISH with 5S rDNA probes (red) and 18S rDNA probe (green). a. Pimelodus absconditus; b. Pimelodus britskii; c. Pimelodus maculatus; d. Pimelodus microstoma; e. Pimelodus mysteriosus; f. Pimelodus ortmanni; g. Pimelodus paranaensis. Scales bar = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3709721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3709721/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
).
</subSubSection>
